# Vercel Web Analytics Configuration

## Summary
Successfully configured Vercel Web Analytics for this Next.js App Router project.

## Changes Made

### Modified Files
- **app/layout.tsx**: Repositioned the `<Analytics />` component to be inside the `<body>` tag

## Details

The `@vercel/analytics` package (v1.6.1) was already installed in the project. However, the `<Analytics />` component was incorrectly placed outside the `<body>` tag, which is not the recommended practice.

### What was fixed:
1. Moved `<Analytics />` component from after the closing `</body>` tag to inside the `<body>` tag
2. Positioned it after the `</ReactLenis>` closing tag, before the `</body>` closing tag
3. This ensures proper analytics tracking while maintaining the existing code structure

### Implementation:
```tsx
<body>
  {/* ... existing content ... */}
  <ReactLenis>
    <Navbar />
    <main>{children}</main>
    <Footer />
    <ClientLayout />
    <Preloader />
    <StickyEmail />
  </ReactLenis>
  <Analytics /> {/* ← Moved inside body tag */}
</body>
```

## Verification

✅ Build completed successfully with `pnpm run build`
✅ TypeScript compilation passed during Next.js build
✅ No changes to dependencies were needed (package already installed)
✅ All existing functionality preserved

## Notes

- The Analytics component is now correctly positioned within the `<body>` tag as per Vercel's best practices
- No additional configuration is needed - analytics will automatically work when deployed to Vercel
- The component will only track in production environments by default
